ge","text":"Indeed, the log scale ticks are still missing.","user":"UM70NJEER","ts":"1611854531.224400","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"SCp8","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Indeed, the log scale ticks are still missing."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1611841313.222000","parent_user_id":"UK1BNFHFV"},{"client_msg_id":"1c74153a-8b00-48fa-b08d-8e888049d4a0","type":"message","text":"well, even an automatic way to do logscale axis, right?","user":"UM70NJEER","ts":"1611854552.224600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"wiX/s","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"well, even an automatic way to do logscale axis, right?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1611841313.222000","parent_user_id":"UK1BNFHFV"},{"client_msg_id":"dc5f4177-7851-4825-b981-82af121aead2","type":"message","text":"the thing is that it's currently so much easier to just `log` your data and then manipulate the ticks, than it is to build the whole backend for arbitrary nonlinear transformations. although pr's are welcome ;)","user":"UK1BNFHFV","ts":"1611855080.225000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"kLe","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"the thing is that it's currently so much easier to just "},{"type":"text","text":"log","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" your data and then manipulate the ticks, than it is to build the whole backend for arbitrary nonlinear transformations. although pr's are welcome ;)"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1611841313.222000","parent_user_id":"UK1BNFHFV"},{"client_msg_id":"3fd61376-0894-460a-b77f-b83354d2ce25","type":"message","text":"I agree, even in the other libraries I usually do `log` to my data and then plotted.","user":"UM70NJEER","ts":"1611855159.225200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"oRkW3","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"I agree, even in the other libraries I usually do "},{"type":"text","text":"log","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" to my data and then plotted."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1611841313.222000","parent_user_id":"UK1BNFHFV"},{"type":"message","text":"here's a very rough attempt at logarithmic minor ticks but that's kind of how it would work\n```struct LogMinorTicks end\n\n\nfunction MakieLayout.get_minor_tickvalues(::LogMinorTicks, tickvalues, vmin, vmax)\n    vals = Float32[]\n    for (lo, hi) in zip(@view(tickvalues[1:end-1]), @view(tickvalues[2:end]))\n        interval = hi-lo\n        steps = log10.(LinRange(10^lo, 10^hi, 10))\n        append!(vals, steps)\n    end\n    vals\nend\n\nscatter(randn(200, 2),\n    axis = (\n        xminorticks = LogMinorTicks(),\n        xminorticksvisible = true,\n        xminorgridvisible = true,\n    ))```","files":[{"id":"F01LXGLBE3S","created":1611856472,"timestamp":1611856472,"name":"image.png","title":"image.png","mimetype":"image/png","filetype":"png","pretty_type":"PNG","user":"UK1BNFHFV","editable":false,"size":127267,"mode":"hosted","is_external":false,"external_type":"","is_public":true,"public_url_shared":false,"display_as_bot":false,"username":"","url_private":"https://files.slack.com/files-pri/T68168MUP-F01LXGLBE3S/image.png","url_private_download":"https://files.slack.com/files-pri/T68168MUP-F01LXGLBE3S/download/image.png","thumb_64":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01LXGLBE3S-dede7227d8/image_64.png","thumb_80":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01LXGLBE3S-dede7227d8/image_80.png","thumb_360":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01LXGLBE3S-dede7227d8/image_360.png","thumb_360_w":360,"thumb_360_h":222,"thumb_480":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01LXGLBE3S-dede7227d8/image_480.png","thumb_480_w":480,"thumb_480_h":296,"thumb_160":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01LXGLBE3S-dede7227d8/image_160.png","thumb_720":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01LXGLB